{
  "text": "Application load balancers operate at layer 7 of the OSI model, meaning they understand HTTP and HTTPS protocols. They can route traffic based on content, such as URL paths, host headers, or query strings. ALBs are highly available by default. SSS automatically distributes them across multiple availability zones. They integrate with Association 2 Manager for SSL termination. And they support WebSocket and HTTP-2P protocols. ALBs are the recommended choice for most web applications, providing a vast routing confrontation. See you soon!",
